What you need to know:  The 14-year old said the younger child, who was his elder brother’s child, had refused to do his homework and he had hit him with a stick on the head, causing him to pass outThe minor died from the head injury upon arriving at the Moi Teaching and Referral Hospital (MTRH) where he was rushed for medical attentionThrough his lawyer Loureen Isiaho, the class seven pupil told the court that family members had discussed the issue and are ready to embrace diversionProsecution said the matter was complex and it needed more time to establish the motive of the killings and whether other people were involved